      section.sg-sect
        h2 The Bare List
        p.
          Use the Bare List object to remove the usual padding and list item markers accompanied by
          (un)ordered lists. The result is a list of items, each on its own line.
          Combine this class with other classes to create a variety of styles.
        figure.sg-fig
          ul.o-ListBare
            li Burns &amp; McDonnell Engineering
            li DIS-TRAN Steel, LLC
            li EDM International
            li Electrical Consultants, Inc.
            li Fabrimet Inc.
            li Falcon Steel Company
          pre.sg-code.sg-code-block.
            &lt;ul class="#[u o-ListBare]"&gt;
              &lt;li&gt;Burns &amp; McDonnell Engineering&lt;/li&gt;
              &lt;li&gt;DIS-TRAN Steel, LLC&lt;/li&gt;
              ...
            &lt;/ul&gt;
      section.sg-sect
        h2 The Flex Grid
        p.
          A Flex Grid is simply a list of items arranged like blocks in a grid.
          It has the structure of a list in that all items share the same container
          (unlike tables where items are in different rows), while at the same time
          appearing like a table with rows and columns.
        p.
          The Flex Grid can be flexible and responsive, adjusting the number of
          columns based on screen size.
          #[mark Remember to set the widths of each item in order to achieve a grid-like appearance.]
        p.
          The container must have the #[code.sg-code .o-GridFlex] class and
          each item must have the #[code.sg-code .o-GridFlex__Item] class.
          To remove normal list styles (padding, bullets, etc.),
          add class #[code.sg-code .o-ListBare] to the container.
